    <data key="d0">Singtel Electronic Mobile Top-up (EMTU)</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LYP98nPBj2A</data>
    <data key="d2">Singtel's next-generation Electronic Mobile Top-up (EMTU) system. It is a mission-critical service designed with strict regulatory compliance, segregating internal and external traffic. The architecture prioritizes high availability, allowing failover between web front-end instances to prevent revenue loss. Key design decisions included moving from proprietary databases to Amazon Aurora for significant cost savings (especially licensing), improved high availability, and automation capabilities. The application is designed to handle bursty workloads, capable of scaling to 50 transactions per second (peak) while averaging 7-10 transactions per second.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
